# Supply-chain hardening: NEVER auto-run dependency lifecycle scripts.
# A trojanized npm package (compromised maintainer account — Shai-Hulud
# sept-2025 pattern) attacks via postinstall/install at BUILD time, not in
# the browser. `npm audit` does NOT catch this (the "official" version IS
# the malicious one). This neutralizes that vector for every dependency.
#
# Only esbuild (postinstall) + sharp (ingestor, install) legitimately need
# their script. They are re-run EXPLICITLY after install via:
#   npm rebuild esbuild --foreground-scripts
#   (ingestor) npm rebuild esbuild sharp --foreground-scripts
# These commands are baked into CI and every deploy one-liner, so a fresh
# `npm install` always produces a working build. See CLAUDE.md
# "PROTOCOLO DEPENDENCIAS / SUPPLY-CHAIN".
ignore-scripts=true
